      "stem_html": "<p>How would you prepare the following compound using a Robinson annulation reaction between a <i>β</i>-diketone and an <i>α</i>,<i>β</i>-unsaturated ketone? Draw the structures of both reactants and the intermediate Michael addition product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcXNZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--00f17c0346cff26127656bf9c2464864a7b7806d/OChem_23_12_004.jpg\" alt=\"Bicyclo[4.4.0]dec-1-ene, with oxo groups on C 3 and C 7, methyl groups on C 2 and C 6, and two methyl groups on C 9.\">",
